A vintage 1960s travel poster style illustration of Singapore's Marina Bay skyline at dusk, with a lone traveler sitting frustrated on a bench, laptop open on their knees, surrounded by invisible radio waves depicted as concentric dotted circles emanating from a sleek exhibition hall in the background. The waves fade and break apart before reaching the traveler, suggesting disconnection. Warm orange and teal color palette with halftone printing texture, bold graphic shapes, and a sense of mid-century optimism clashing with modern digital disappointment.
